Compiling this code
```scala
object Error {
  def f {
    case class X(b: Boolean = false)
    val x = X()
  }
}
```
with scalac 2.8.1.final yields:
```scala
Error.scala:4: error: forward reference extends over definition of value x
    val x = X()
            ^
one error found
```

This seems similar to ticket scala/bug#2489, but this has been fixed and the code from that ticket compiles without errors.

